Sure! Here's a simple 'if-else' structure in Java:

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int x = 10;

        if (x > 5) {
            System.out.println("x is greater than 5");
        } else {
            System.out.println("x is not greater than 5");
        }
    }
}
```

This code prints a different message based on the value of variable `x`. If `x` is greater than 5, it prints "x is greater than 5". Otherwise, it prints "x is not greater than 5".
